<header>
	Read the writing task on the left and answer the questions on the right. In some cases, there is more than one correct answer.
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <p align="left"><b>1.</b>  Who do you have to write to?<g id="t1">A.  a relative</g><g id="t2">B.  an acquaintance</g><g id="t3">C.  a stranger</g><g id="t4">D.  a friend</g><g id="t5">E.  a colleague</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>2.</b>  What style of letter should you write?<g id="t6">A.  formal</g><g id="t7">B.  informal</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>3.</b>  What do you have to do in this letter?<g id="t8">A.  make a complaint</g><g id="t9">B.  make an apology</g><g id="t10">C.  give reasons</g><g id="t11">D.  make a request</g><g id="t12">E.  make an application</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>4.</b>  How many points do you have to coverin this letter?<g id="t13">A.  one</g><g id="t14">B.  two</g><g id="t15">C.  three</g><g id="t16">D.  four</g><g id="t17">E.  five</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>5.</b>  Which of the following would it beappropriate to include in this letter?<g id="t18">A.  reference to the day and time of the original appointment</g><g id="t19">B.  reference to how long ago you made the original appointment</g><g id="t20">C.  the reason why you missed the appointment</g><g id="t21">D.  the reason you still want to see the immigration officer</g><g id="t22">E.  a suggestion as to an alternative day and time for the appointment</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>6.</b>  According to the writing task, what doyou have to ask in this letter?<g id="t23">A.  if you can cancel the appointment</g><g id="t24">B.  if you can rearrange the appointment</g><g id="t25">C.  if you can explain why you missed the appointment</g><g id="t26">D.  if you can see a different immigration officer</g><g id="t27">E.  if you need to make a new appointment</g></p>
  <p align="left">
    <font size="2"/>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="readingText">
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#0000ff">
      <b>Writing Task 1</b>
    </font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">You should spend about 20 minutes on this task.</p>
  <p align="left">
    <b>You missed an appointment at the immigration department because you were involved in an accident.</b>
  </p>
  <p align="left">
    <b>Write a letter to the immigration officer. Apologise for missing the appointment and explain why you missed it. Ask if you can make a new appointment.</b>
  </p>
  <p align="left">You should write at least 150 words.</p>
  <p align="left">You do <b>NOT</b> need to write your own address.</p>
  <p align="left">
    <font color="#000000">Begin your letter as follows:</font>
  </p>
  <p align="left">Dear Sir/Madam,</p>
  <p align="left">
    <font size="2"/>
  </p>
